<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Firm To Build Indigenously Designed Aircraft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0501084894 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0000 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0501084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The IPTN [Nusantara Aviation Industries] will 
begin production this year of the N-250 aircraft, powered by 
turbo-prop engines. The aircraft, suitable for short flights, 
was designed by Indonesian technicians. Research and Technology 
Minister B.J. Habibie disclosed this in Jakarta yesterday when 
he met with the Indonesian ambassadors-designate and consuls 
general-designate to several countries. The minister said IPTN 
is planning to produce one N-250 plane every week, adding that 
IPTN will produce wide-bodied jets by the year 2006. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

