<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister To Visit Cambodia 12-14 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0501084494 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0501084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Chuan Likphai will visit Cambodia 
next week to strengthen bilateral relations between Thailand and 
the Royal Government of Cambodia. The three-day visit, 
scheduled for 12-14 January, will be the first visit to that 
country by the prime minister. 
  Government Spokesman Aphisit Wetchachiwa says that Thailand 
has played a vital role in the reconstruction of Cambodia. The 
government has provided economic assistance to Thai business 
people who earlier concluded agreements with various Cambodian 
factions. Mr. Aphisit says that the ongoing fighting between the 
elected Cambodian Government and the Khmer Rouge will not affect 
the visit to Cambodia by Prime Minister Chuan. However, he 
says, among the neighboring countries of Cambodia, Thailand will 
be most affected by the fighting. He reaffirms that Thailand 
has always complied with the United Nations resolutions on 
Cambodia. 

</TEXT>

